      <titleblock previous-project="marble-clock" next-project="binary-counter">The incredible inside-out pinball machine</titleblock>
      
      <block layout="text-left">
        <text>
          <p>Once upon a time I bought a derelict pinball machine.</p>
          <p>According to the previous owner it was "beyond repair"...</p>
          <p>I was able to get my hands on the original electric schematic, so I started restoring this beautiful piece of machinery.</p>
        </text>
        <carousel>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-original-1.jpg"/>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-original-2.jpg"/>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-original-3.jpg"/>
          <image href="pinball/schematic.jpg"/>
        </carousel>
      </block>

      <block layout="text-right">
        <text>
          <p>End result after more than two years: the pinball machine was fully functioning again!</p>
          <p>This is how it looks now.</p>
          <p>It was too big to keep. I gave it to a friend who has a large man-cave.</p>
        </text>
        <carousel>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-1.jpg"/>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-2.jpg"/>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-3.jpg"/>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-4.jpg"/>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-5.jpg"/>
          <image href="pinball/pinball-6.jpg"/>
        </carousel>
      </block>
      
      <block layout="text-left">
